        <p>Real data from liver tissue in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR23">23</xref>] indicates a linear relationship between the logarithm of average total read counts and that of the sample standard deviation of total read counts within a gene across SNPs. Real data also indicates a roughly linear relationship between the logarithm of average total read counts and that of the sample standard deviation of total read counts within a SNP across four replicates. To simulate <italic>n</italic><sub><italic>gjk</italic></sub>, we utilized these two linear relationships. Specifically, let <inline-formula id="IEq8"><alternatives><tex-math id="M15">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
