      <p>Due to the expense of sample collection and sequencing experiments, most laboratories can only afford a few biological replicates, such as <italic>K</italic>= 3 or 4. In addition, the number of available SNPs in a gene also depends on the diversity between parental alleles. Often, only a small number of genes contain a large number of SNPs. Thus, for most genes, the estimates of <italic>β</italic><sub><italic>g</italic></sub>, <inline-formula id="IEq39"><alternatives><tex-math id="M79">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
