				\begin{document}$\mathcal {M}$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M112"><mml:mi mathvariant="script">ℳ</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2019_3141_Article_IEq54.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> that maximizes the marginal likelihood <italic>P</italic>(<bold>y</bold><sup><italic>g</italic></sup>|<italic>m</italic>,<bold>n</bold><sup><italic>g</italic></sup>), which, when comparing two models, is equivalent to choosing the model <italic>m</italic> using the Bayes factor. Let <bold>b</bold><sub><italic>g</italic></sub> denote all random effects; that is, <inline-formula id="IEq55"><alternatives><tex-math id="M113">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
